This paper deals with the construction of new self-dual codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of tailbiting convolutional codes, which is a topic in coding theory and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves the manipulation of circulant matrices, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The codes constructed in the paper may also have applications in signal processing (cs.SI) and network coding (cs.NI).
